summary: I can literally look at any picture of Michael Sheen, and unless it is distinctly from something I’ve seen him in or can...
body: I can literally look at any picture of Michael Sheen, and unless it is distinctly from something I’ve seen him in or can recognize, I can’t tell you when it was taken or how old he was at the time. Which is so weird and a bit horrifying to me. Like my mam had me watch Bright Young Things for the first time a couple weeks ago and I’m just like, “Oh yeah, this is definitely from the 1980s.” Bitch, no, I looked it up and that movie was made in 2003. A picture of him from the actual 1980s? I thought it was like 10 years ago. And then I saw a picture today from about 10 years ago and I’m like, “Ooh, this is recent.” No, it wasn’t. What even is Michael Sheen? Is he human? Does he understand how one is supposed to age, or does he just wake up and decide, “Oh, I’m gonna look 30 today, and tomorrow I’ll look 50 and I think next Tuesday I’ll look 45″?
